# Before Writing useEffect

Source: [You really, really don't need an effect](https://neciudan.dev/you-really-really-dont-need-an-effect) · [React docs](https://react.dev/learn/you-might-not-need-an-effect)

**Ask one question: Is this syncing with an external system?**

External (effect OK): WebSocket, browser APIs (`IntersectionObserver`, `navigator.onLine`), third-party widgets, DOM measurements, timers with cleanup.

NOT external: props, state, derived values, user events (click, submit, change).

## Decision tree — check before writing an effect

| Case | Don't | Do |
|------|-------|-----|
| Transforming data | `useEffect` + `setState` | Compute inline, or `useMemo` if expensive |
| User event | Effect watching a flag | Logic in the event handler |
| Reset state on prop change | `useEffect(() => setState(prop), [prop])` | `<Component key={prop} />` |
| Fetching data | Raw `useEffect` + `fetch` alone | TanStack Query; if effect, add stale-response cleanup |
| Notify parent | Effect on state change | Call callback in the event handler |
| Chained effects | Multiple effects cascading `setState` | Reset/derive in one event handler or `useReducer` |
| External store | `useEffect` + subscribe + `setState` | `useSyncExternalStore` |

## Rules

- NEVER `useEffect(() => setSomething(derived), [dep])`
- NEVER use effects for click/submit/change handlers
- NEVER reset local state on prop change without trying `key` first
- For debounced inputs: local state updates immediately; debounce only persistence/API calls
- ALWAYS add cleanup when subscribing to external systems
- Name effect functions for readability; use `useLayoutEffect` for DOM measurements before paint

## Valid effect example

```tsx
useEffect(function connectToChatRoom() {
  const connection = createConnection(roomId);
  connection.connect();
  return () => connection.disconnect();
}, [roomId]);
```

## ESLint enforcement

`eslint-plugin-react-you-might-not-need-an-effect` is enabled (warn) via `eslint.config.mjs`. Run `npm run lint`. React Hooks `set-state-in-effect` is also enabled via `eslint-config-next`.
